asic EPS | Diluted EPS | Basic Shares (in millions) | Diluted Shares (in millions) |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| **Three Months Ended Mar 31, 2026** | $(4,276) | $(1.27) | $(1.27) | 3,884 | 3,884 |\n| **Three Months Ended Mar 31, 2025** | $(528) | $(0.18) | $(0.18) | 2,875 | 2,875 |\n| **Year Ended Dec 31, 2025** | $(4,937) | $(1.69) | $(1.69) | 2,926 | 2,926 |\n| **Year Ended Dec 31, 2024** | $791 | $0.01 | $0.00 | 2,848 | 9,956 |\n| **Year Ended Dec 31, 2023** | $(4,628) | $(1.68) | $(1.68) | 2,759 | 2,759 |\n\n---\n\n### 3. Unaudited Pro Forma Net Loss Per Share\nThe pro forma EPS gives effect to the Preferred Conversion, Class C Reclassification, and charter effectiveness as if they occurred on **January 1, 2025**.\n\n| Pro Forma Components | Three Months Ended Mar 31, 2026 | Year Ended Dec 31, 2025 |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| **Numerator:** | | |\n| Net loss attributable to common shareholders | $(4,947) | $(4,937) |\n| *Adjustment:* Reverse deemed dividend on Preferred Stock | 565 | — |\n| **Pro Forma Net Loss** | **$(4,382)** | **$(4,937)** |\n| **Denominator:** | | |\n| Weighted average shares (Basic & Diluted) | 3,884 | 2,926 |\n| *Adjustment:* Preferred Conversion assumption | 6,723 | 6,723 |\n| **Pro Forma Weighted Average Shares** | **10,607** | **9,649** |\n| **Pro Forma EPS (Basic & Diluted)** | **$(0.41)** | **$(0.51)** |\n\n---\n\n### 4. EPS Reconciliation (Numerator & Denominator)\nThe reconciliation below highlights the adjustments made for participating securities, deemed dividends, and assumed conversions (illustrated using the **Year Ended December 31, 2024**, where diluted EPS differed from basic EPS):\n\n**Numerator (in millions):**\n*   **Net Income:** $791\n*   *Less:* Deemed dividend ¹: $(80)\n*   *Less:* Earnings allocated to participating securities: $(693)\n*   **Net Income attributable to common shareholders (Basic):** $18\n*   *Add:* Effect of assumed conversion of Preferred Stock: $3\n*   **Net Income attributable to common shareholders (Diluted):** $21\n\n**Denominator (in millions):**\n*   **Weighted average shares (Basic):** 2,848\n*   *Add:* Conversion of Preferred Stock: 6,771\n*   *Add:* Exercise of stock options: 292\n*   *Add:* Conversion of RSUs: 45\n*   **Weighted average shares (Diluted):** 9,956\n\n> **¹ Deemed Dividend Note:** The excess of fair market value over the consideration transferred for the repurchase of SpaceX Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock was treated as a deemed dividend. This resulted in a decrease to net income (or an increase to net loss) attributable to common shareholders in the EPS calculation.\n\n---\n\n### 5. Anti-Dilutive Securities Excluded\nThe following potentially dilutive securities (on an as-converted basis) were excluded from the diluted EPS calculations because their inclusion would have been anti-dilutive due to the net losses incurred or the mechanics of the two-class method:\n\n| Security (in millions) | Q1 2026 | Q1 2025 | FY 2025 | FY 2024 | FY 2023 |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| **xAI Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock** | — | 1,155 | 1,369 | — | 537 |\n| **SpaceX Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock** | 6,723 | 6,760 | 6,733 | — | 6,780 |\n| **Share-based compensation** | 598 | 674 | 623 | 18 | 767 |\n\n*(Note: The table above also excludes 1,319.1 million and 14.3 million share-based compensation awards outstanding as of specific periods that were not yet vested or met performance conditions).*',
