N.V., Banco BTG Pactual S.A. – Cayman Branch,** and **Mirae Asset Securities Co., Ltd.** are not broker-dealers registered with the SEC.\n*   Consequently, they are strictly prohibited from making sales of any Class A shares in the United States or to U.S. persons, except in compliance with applicable U.S. laws and regulations.\n\n### 4. The Underwriters Syndicate\n*   **Representatives (Lead Underwriters):** Goldman Sachs & Co. LLC, Morgan Stanley & Co. LLC, BofA Securities, Inc., Citigroup Global Markets Inc., and J.P. Morgan Securities LLC.\n*   **Syndicate Members:** Barclays, Deutsche Bank, RBC Capital Markets, UBS, Wells Fargo, BTG Pactual, ING, Macquarie, Mirae Asset, Mizuho, Santander, Allen & Co., Cantor, Needham, Raymond James, SG Americas, Societe Generale, Stifel, and William Blair.\n*   **Stabilization Agent:** Morgan Stanley & Co. LLC.\n\n### 5. Determination of the Offering Price\n*   Prior to this offering, there was no public market for the Class A common stock. \n*   The IPO price was determined through **negotiations between the company and the representatives**. \n*   **Factors considered** included: prevailing market conditions, the future prospects of the company and its industry, historical financial and operating performance, management\'s assessment, and market valuations of comparable companies.\n*   *Note: The exact assumed IPO price midpoint and total share counts are redacted (left blank) in the provided preliminary prospectus excerpts.*\n\n### 6. IPO Share Structure & Capitalization\n*   **Dual-Class Voting Structure:**\n    *   **Class A Common Stock:** Entitled to **1 vote** per share.\n    *   **Class B Common Stock:** Entitled to **10 votes** per share. Both classes will vote together as a single class on all matters.\n*   **Pre-IPO Capitalization Adjustments:**\n    *   **Class C Reclassification:** All outstanding Class C common stock will be reclassified into Class A common stock.\n    *   **Preferred Conversion:** All outstanding preferred stock will be converted into a mix of Class A and Class B common stock.\n*   **Listing:** The Class A common stock will be listed on **Nasdaq** and **Nasdaq Texas** under the symbol **"SPCX"**.\n\n### 7. Share Allocation & Directed Share Program\n*   **Directed Share Program:** At the company\'s request, up to a specified percentage of shares are reserved for sale at the IPO price to employees, management-identified persons, business partners, and friends/family of management. **These shares will not be subject to lock-up restrictions.**\n*   **Retail Investor Access:** Shares will be allocated to retail investors via online brokerage platforms (Charles Schwab, Fidelity, Robinhood, SoFi, and E*TRADE by Morgan Stanley). Purchases will occur at the exact same IPO price and time as institutional investors.\n*   **Founder Lock-Up:** The Founder is explicitly excluded from any early release provisions during the extended lock-up period.\n\n### 8. Price Stabilization & Short Sales\nTo facilitate the offering and stabilize the stock price post-IPO, the underwriters (led by Morgan Stanley as stabilization agent) may engage in the following activities:\n*   **Covered Short Sales:** Selling more shares than obligated, up to the over-allotment option amount. This is closed by either exercising the over-allotment option or buying shares in the open market.\n*   **Naked Short Sales:** Selling shares in excess of the over-allotment option. This *must* be closed by purchasing shares in the open market. Underwriters typically create a naked short position if they are concerned about downward price pressure in the open market after pricing.\n*   **Open Market Purchases:** The underwriters may bid for and purchase shares in the open market to stabilize or maintain the price above independent market levels. They are not required to do so and may stop at any time.',
